  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a pan over medium heat. Add onion, garlic, cumin seeds, coriander seeds, green chilies, and bay leaves.",
    "Stir-fry until onions turn translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add lamb pieces to the pan and fry for another 10 minutes, turning occasionally.",
    "Pour in turmeric powder, garam masala, and Maggi Masala. Stir well to coat all lamb pieces evenly.",
    "Reduce heat to low-medium. Pour in soy sauce or tamari, Greek yogurt (if using), and cover the pan.",
    "Simmer for about 20-30 minutes until the meat is tender and most of the liquid has evaporated.",
    "Serve hot with steamed basmati rice."
  ],
